      "comment": "LAUBERHORN (4) looks the clear horse to beat on debut in a very winnable maiden. He's a gelding by Extreme Choice for the Price & Kent Jnr yard who has been jumping out and trialling very well for this. He's been heavily supported in early markets and that's a very strong push for top connections. INTERROGATE (3) has shown some ability in two runs to date, finding a race in town a bit tough last time after a good debut. He can be challenging. GALACTIC FORCE (1) was just fair as favourite last time, dry ground here could be beneficial. LAUNDERING (5) is a Contributer gelding on debut who can run well for the Templeton yard.",
